name: Jill

description: We had to fend off a whole family of raccoons that wanted to steal Irma's eggs (111 of them). Raccoons are some of the natural predators of sea turtle eggs and babies, but due to a decline in bigger predators like coyotes, the raccoon populations are now out of control and are endangering already endangered species like sea turtles. If you are interested to read about what else we are doing, you can follow our field work on http://plotkinlabtamu.wix.com/plotkinlab#!blog/b7vfl.
name: Irma

description: Susan is named for Susan G. Komen; Peoria native and breast cancer survivor.
name: Susan

description: Gale is a female short-finned pilot whale that was brought to SeaWorld Orlando as part of a mass stranding of other cetaceans off the coast of St. Petersburg, Fla. in July 2017. After a short rehabilitation, she was successfully returned off the west coast of Florida in August 2017.
name: Gale

description: Edith is our very last turtle for this season and named in honor of the person who showed the most spirit across our school outreach program to increase #OceanLiteracy. If you are interested to read about what else we are doing, you can follow our field work on http://plotkinlabtamu.wix.com/plotkinlab#!blog/b7vfl.
name: Edith

description: After a heavy thunderstorm, we went patrolling and the first turtle we found was Tony. Tony is named in honor of Conservationist, Scientist, and Animal Hero Tony Amos, who passed away recently. Tony was the founder of the ARK, an animal rehabilitation center that was severely damaged by Hurricane Harvey.  If you are interested to read about what else we are doing, you can follow our field work on http://plotkinlabtamu.wix.com/plotkinlab#!blog/b7vfl.
name: Tony

description: Susan laid her eggs right in front of a huge beach resort and was a little bit disoriented by the hotel’s light when she crawled back to the water. She laid a total of 114 eggs and we are looking forward to seeing her travel to her next destination. If you are interested to read about what else we are doing, you can follow our field work on http://plotkinlabtamu.wix.com/plotkinlab#!blog/b7vfl.
name: Susan

description: Todd Goggins named Lesley after his Grandmother.
name: Lesley

description: Sad pictures of the destruction in Houston and the Caribbean islands by the two recent hurricanes have haunted us, and we named our 8th turtle “Harmony”, inspired by a Houstonian student affected by Hurricane Harvey. In her own words: “Houston needs all the Harmony we can get with everyone helping each other recover from this devastation.” If you are interested to read about what else we are doing, you can follow our field work on http://plotkinlabtamu.wix.com/plotkinlab#!blog/b7vfl.
name: Harmony

description: Maia is the third turtle to be tracked from Kyparissia Bay in 2018. In Greek mythology, Maia is the daughter of Atlas and the mother of Hermes (the god of communication and connectivity).
name: Maia

description: This fish was tagged by Dr. Camrin Braun and Dr. Peter Gaube from the University of Washington as part of the Ocean Twilight Zone project at the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution and Operation Deep Drop, in partnership with Wildlife Computers. Rex was named by Dr. Peter Gaube's youngest son who is a fish fanatic with an insatiable interest in the oceans. For more information and to contribute to Operation Deep Drop visit the GoFundMe page.
name: Rex

description: Don’t miss your chance to visit Dinosaur Time Trek: Shark Edition and travel to pre-history for a roaring, stomping, roam-through experience like no other.  Time trekkers can jump into the world of dinos, with hands-on exhibits sure to delight even the smallest Microraptor in your brood. Get a glimpse into Shark Bay, powered by OCEARCH, and see a replica of the famous Mary Lee from the OCEARCH family along with other mysterious prehistoric creatures that are still alive today. Thanks to our partnership with OCEARCH – track real life sharks and view live footage from recent expeditions. #DontFearTheFin
length: Stay as long as youd like!
name: Dinosaur TimeTrek  Shark

description: Ema was tagged by a collaboration of researchers from Saving Our Sharks, Texas State Aquarium, INAPESCA and Mote Marine Laboratory. Scientists hope to learn more about the movement patterns, connectivity between populations, feeding behavior and potential breeding areas with regards to the species in this area.
name: Ema

description: Holly is the sixth green sea turtle tagged of the 2019 season. Researchers from the Sanibel-Captiva Conservation Foundation tagged Holly after she successfully laid a nest on Sanibel Island, Florida. She will be part of a study to learn more about the post-nesting movements and migratory pathways of green sea turtles that nest on the gulf coast of Florida. All research authorized by Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission.
name: Holly

description: Last but not least we have Elaia; the final turtle to be tracked by ARCHELON in 2018. Elaia is a coastal village at the core nesting area of Kyparissia Bay. Elaia was also a goddess half-angel half-demon in Greek mythology, often accompanied by nymphs and elves (xotika).
name: Elaia

description: rtfre

Cypress is an adult, reproductive female American alligator living in the Okefenokee Swamp, the largest blackwater swamp in North America. By collecting data on her movements using satellite tags we are hoping to better understand how female alligators use the swamp ecosystem and how their home ranges vary with seasonality. We are also hoping to use her movement data to locate her nesting site.
name: Cypress

description: Chris Fischer named Lyla Grace after his daughter.
name: Lyla Grace

description: This fish was tagged by Dr. Camrin Braun and Dr. Peter Gaube from the University of Washington as part of the Ocean Twilight Zone project at the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution and Operation Deep Drop, in partnership with Wildlife Computers. Oliver was named by Dr. Simon Thorrold (WHOI) after his grandfather who was an avid fisherman and passionate about ocean conservation. For more information and to contribute to Operation Deep Drop visit the GoFundMe page.
name: Oliver

description: Shark Koru had a curled lower caudal fin, so she was named after the spiral shape based on the appearance of a new unfurling silver fern frond, an important Mori symbol. The tiger sharks around Norfolk Island were tagged by an international team of scientists from Australia and the USA, to understand what areas around the island the sharks use. This is part of a larger research program to determine if these sharks hang around the offshore islands where they are tagged, or if they travel over to Australia, New Zealand, or further.
name: Koru

description: Coral, an endangered olive ridley sea turtle, was rescued after being found stranded Oct. 20, 2017 by a member of the public on a beach near Salishan on the Oregon coast. When rescued, she was emaciated, weak and suffering from hypothermia, and was taken to the Seattle Aquarium, WA the only sea turtle rehabilitation facility. The aquarium’s staff immediately began lifesaving medical treatment including addressing serious bacterial infections. Coral’s condition slowly stabilized and on Jan. 26, 2018, she was flown by the U.S. Coast Guard to San Diego seven months of rehabilitation at SeaWorld San Diego’s Animal Health and Rescue Center.
name: Coral

description: Kekoa means brave. Kekoa was tagged by the Maui Ocean center, which is the Hawaiian Aquarium, dedicated to promoting fostering and understanding of the Hawaiian Marine environment and the relationship to the host culture to that environment. They are advocates for better understanding of sharks, rays and Hawaiian green Sea Turtles.
name: Kekoa

description: We had moved to a different nesting beach (Hacienda Baru) and after three nights with many poachers on the beach, we were able to outrun them and found Faith. She did not have any follicles or eggs left in her ovaries and oviducts, so she is seemingly done nesting for the season. If you are interested to read about what else we are doing, you can follow our field work on http://plotkinlabtamu.wix.com/plotkinlab#!blog/b7vfl.
name: Faith

description: Neda is the first turtle tracked by ARCHELON in Kyparissia Bay in 2018. In Greek mythology, Neda was a nymph of waters (nymphs were regarded as divine spirits animating nature). Neda is also the name of a river at the core nesting area of Kyparissia Bay!
name: Neda

description: This fish was tagged by Dr. Camrin Braun and Dr. Peter Gaube from the University of Washington as part of the Ocean Twilight Zone project at the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution and Operation Deep Drop, in partnership with Wildlife Computers. Anthony was named after Capt. Anthony "Tony" DiGiulian, an accomplished angler and guide who has dedicated his life to helping people experience the joy of fishing through his work with numerous foundations and organizations. For more information and to contribute to Operation Deep Drop visit the GoFundMe page.
name: Anthony

description: Shark David was the smallest male tagged on an expedition by collaborating scientists at Norfold Island. He is named after the trip coordinator Mark Scott’s young son. The tiger sharks around Norfolk Island were tagged by an international team of scientists from Australia and the USA, to understand what areas around the island the sharks use. This is part of a larger research program to determine if these sharks hang around the offshore islands where they are tagged, or if they travel over to Australia, New Zealand, or further.
name: David

description: The Judge was tagged by scientists of The Nature Conservancy using a SPOT tag during a shark fisheries-independent monitoring cruise off Sarasota Bay in Florida in collaboration with Mote Marine Laboratory. “The Judge” is named after Judge Roy Bean, a legendary Justice of Peace who called himself "The Law West of the Pecos [River]" in the late 1800s along the Rio Grande on southwest Texas.
name: The Judge

description: Chris Fischer named Madiba after Nelson Mandela. Madiba was caught and killed on a drumline at Sunwich Port on the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast in January, 2013.
name: Madiba

description: DESCRIPTION
name: ACK

description: SouthJaw is a juvenile male Tiger Shark tagged by scientists at the University of South Alabama (USA) and the Dauphin Island Sea Lab. SouthJaw was named by USA undergraduate students as a tribute to SouthPaw, the University Mascot.
name: SouthJaw

description: After rainy days and a Tsunami warning, we finally found Lady Kemma. Our last female to be tagged in Playa Hermosa. Her name is also inspired by a Houstonian teacher part of our outreach program #TAMUSeaTurtleTrackingProject, whose dear friend was flooded out during hurricane Harvey, but who is fighting back to recover and get back to teaching. If you are interested to read about what else we are doing, you can follow our field work on http://plotkinlabtamu.wix.com/plotkinlab#!blog/b7vfl.
name: Lady Kemma

description: Sabrina was double-tagged by Mote Marine Laboratory scientists with a fin-mounted SPOT5 transmitter, for near real time location information, as well as a pop-up archival tag. Together these satellite tags will provide data that will contribute to our understanding of the movement, migration, and habitat utilization of Bull Sharks along the Florida Gulf coast.
name: Sabrina
